Appendix F: Additional Mathematical Derivations

F.1 Derivation of the Discretized Thermal Dynamics

Starting from the PDE:

\rho c_p \frac{\partial T}{\partial t} = \nabla \cdot (k\nabla T) + q_{\text{aero}} - \nabla \cdot q_{\text{cool}} - q_{\text{rad}}.

Using finite volumes with cell i of volume V_i, the left‑hand side becomes \rho c_p V_i \dot{T}_i. The conductive term is approximated by

\int_{\Omega_i} \nabla \cdot (k\nabla T) dV \approx \sum_{j\in\mathcal{N}_i} \frac{k_{ij}(T_j - T_i)}{d_{ij}} A_{ij},

where d_{ij} is the distance between cell centers and A_{ij} the interface area. Define k_{ij} = (k_i + k_j)/2. The cooling term is

\int_{\Omega_i} \nabla \cdot q_{\text{cool}} dV \approx A_i q_{\text{cool},i},

where q_{\text{cool},i} is the net cooling flux from the actuators. The radiative term is A_i \epsilon_i \sigma (T_i^4 - T_\infty^4). Dividing by \rho c_p V_i yields the semi‑discrete equation:

\dot{T}_i = \frac{1}{\rho c_p V_i} \left[ \sum_{j\in\mathcal{N}_i} k_{ij} A_{ij}/d_{ij} (T_j - T_i) + A_i q_{\text{aero},i} - A_i q_{\text{cool},i} - A_i \epsilon_i \sigma (T_i^4 - T_\infty^4) \right].

Define k_{ij}^{\text{eff}} = k_{ij} A_{ij}/(\rho c_p V_i d_{ij}). Then

\dot{T}_i = \sum_{j\in\mathcal{N}_i} k_{ij}^{\text{eff}} (T_j - T_i) + \frac{A_i}{\rho c_p V_i} q_{\text{aero},i} - \frac{A_i}{\rho c_p V_i} q_{\text{cool},i} - \frac{A_i \epsilon_i \sigma}{\rho c_p V_i} (T_i^4 - T_\infty^4).

For linearization, we write \dot{T}_i = f_i(T_i, \mathbf{u}_i) + \sum_j \kappa_{ij}(T_j - T_i) and then define the state vector \mathbf{x}_i = [T_i; \dot{T}_i]. The derivative \dot{\dot{T}}_i is obtained by differentiating the above, leading to the second‑order form with \mathbf{A}_i containing terms like -\kappa_{ii} and -\frac{4A_i \epsilon_i \sigma}{\rho c_p V_i} T_i^3 from the radiation linearization.

F.2 Derivation of Entropy Production

The entropy balance for a control volume is:

\frac{dS}{dt} = \int_{\partial V} \frac{\mathbf{q}}{T} \cdot \mathbf{n} \, dA + \int_V \frac{\dot{q}_{\text{gen}}}{T} \, dV + \dot{S}_{\text{gen}},

where \dot{S}_{\text{gen}} \ge 0 is the entropy production. For the thermal subsystem, the entropy production rate can be expressed as

\dot{S}_{\text{gen}} = \int_V \frac{k}{T^2} \|\nabla T\|^2 \, dV + \int_V \frac{(q_{\text{aero}} - \nabla \cdot q_{\text{cool}})}{T} \, dV - \int_{\partial V} \frac{q_{\text{rad}}}{T} \, dA.

After discretization, we obtain the sum given in Theorem 7.

F.3 Linearization of Radiation Term

The term q_{\text{rad}} = \epsilon \sigma (T^4 - T_\infty^4) is linearized around T_0 as:

q_{\text{rad}} \approx \epsilon \sigma (4T_0^3 (T - T_0) + T_0^4 - T_\infty^4).

Thus in the state matrix \mathbf{A}_i, the contribution from radiation appears as a term -\frac{4A_i \epsilon_i \sigma T_0^3}{\rho c_p V_i} in the \dot{T}_i equation, and in the second‑order model it appears in both the T_i and \dot{T}_i dynamics.



